free: #e A boy, a dog, and a frog are in the house. They are in the boy's room
#c 一個男孩、一隻狗和一隻青蛙在房子裡。他們在這男孩的房間裡。
#n tqiyan 原指"睡覺之處"，此處引申為房間。
#e I saw a moon. Is this Ok?
#c 我看到一個月亮。可以嗎？
#e The boy and the dog were looking at the frog in the bottle together.
#c 男孩和狗一起看在瓶子裡的青蛙。
#n oda 為"經過"之詞根，可根據情境譯為 "事情"、"經歷"、"故事"等語意。
#e Now, I'm going to tell a story about a boy and a dog.
#c 現在呢，我要來說一個關於一個男孩和狗的故事。
#n 此處mi應是尚未講完的mita "看"。
#e The dog and the dog are looking at the frog in the bottle.
#c 狗和這個小男孩在看在罐子裡的青蛙。
#e And this dog, it is trying to catch (the frog).
#c 那麼這隻狗呢，他就想去抓(青蛙)。
#e And the boy was very happy, seeing this. He was laughing too.
#c 這個小男孩看了很高興，也笑了。
#e Sitting on his chair, he was looking at the frog.
#c 他坐在他的椅子椅子上，看著青蛙。
#e It was night now, and we could see the moon from the house.
#c 到了晚上，我們從房子看到月亮。
#n bobo 原意為"在...之上"。在言談中其功能為表"之後"。
#e Afterwards, the kid saw the moon from the window of his house, from his room.
#c 之後，這個小孩在房子裡，從房間的窗戶看到的月亮。
#e The boy was sleeping on the bed, in his house.
#c 這小孩在房裡的床上睡覺。
#n pala 原指原住民所編織的布匹，此處引申為"被褥"之意。
#e His dog was sleeping with him. He (the dog) was sleeping on the boy's quilt.
#c 他的狗也跟他一起睡。他(狗)睡在小男孩的被子上。
#e Since they, the dog and the boy, were sleeping, the frog climbed out of the bottle, and came outside.
#c 因為狗狗和小男孩在睡覺，這隻青蛙就從瓶子裡爬出來，而來到了外面。
#e The dog and the boy woke up. They looked at the bottle, and the frog wasn't there. He had escaped!
#c 狗狗和小男孩醒來後，他們便又看著瓶子。但是青蛙卻不在那裏。他已經逃走了。
#n sklui 可指 "驚嚇" 或 "驚訝"。此處為後者之語意。
#e The dog and the boy were surprised to find that the frog had escaped.
#c 這個男孩和狗看到青蛙逃走了很驚訝。
#e The boy then cried out, "wa ...". He was surprised, and he stared to look for the frog.
#c 男孩於是「哇」的叫著。驚嚇之餘，他開始尋找青蛙。
#n klaun 主焦形式為 mkela "知道"。受焦形式於句首表 "可能" 之意。
#n so 表達說者於言談中之不確定性，一般譯為 "像"。
#e Perhaps it (the frog) had gone hiding in his shoes!
#c 青蛙可能躲在他的鞋子裡。
#e So the boy grabbed the top of his shoes and looked into them, but the frog is not in his shoes.
#c 這個男孩於是拿起了他的鞋子並往裡看，但青蛙並不在裡面。
#e And the boy's dog, he also put his neck and head into the bottle to look for the frog.
#c 而他的狗呢，也伸著脖子和頭到罐子裡去找青蛙。
#e The dog's head was stuck in the bottle, and he just couldn't get his head out of it, since his neck was stuck.
#c 狗的頭被卡在罐子裡，而且實在是拔不出來，因為他的脖子被卡住了。
#e The boy opened the window and kept calling for the frog.
#c 小男孩打開窗戶不斷地呼喊著青蛙。
#e He was calling. "Where did you go?" he probably said this
#c 小男孩呼喊著青蛙「你去哪裡了？」他是這麼說的吧。
#e The boy's look seems to show that he was panicing.
#c 小男孩的眼神好像是驚慌到了。
#n 此處sklui應指"驚慌"。
#e Why did he panic? Because both his dog and the bottle fell onto the window.
#c 為什麼驚嚇呢? 因為他的狗和瓶子一起掉落到了窗戶上。
#e So the boy was shocked. "Ayu!" he cried.
#c 所以小男孩驚嚇到了。「唉呀！」他叫出聲來。
#n kucu 為日語借詞，重疊後 k<m>kucu成為動詞"穿鞋"。
#n sapic為族語之"鞋子"原指出外打仗時，綁在腳趾上由鹿皮所製作之鞋套。
#e So the boy put on his shoes and came outside. He hugged the dog and comforted him. They are very close to each other.
#c 所以，小孩就穿鞋到外面去。他抱起狗並且安撫他。他們非常要好。
#e The dog thought: "Thank you very much!" licking the boy's cheek with his teeth.
#c 這隻狗想著：「真感謝你。」於是他便用舌頭舔這個小孩。
#n nganguc 通常指住家外圍，而ngerac則指部落之外。前者距離較短，後者較長。
#e Then they go outside to call for the frog.
#c 接著他們到外面去呼喊青蛙。
#e There is a big tree next to his house.
#c 他的房子旁邊有棵大樹。
#e The boy calls for the frog loudly, and so does the dog.
#c 男孩大聲地叫喊青蛙，而狗也是。
#e Then they walked a little farther, and arrived at the bottom of a tree.
#c 接著他們走遠一點，來到了樹下。
#n pusu qhuni 字面上指"樹根"，此處為"樹下"之意。
#n 此處cudu應為口誤。cudu指"毒藤"，而rudu方指"窩"。
#e They saw a bee hive, and there were bees inside.
#c 他們看見一個蜂窩，裡面有蜜蜂。
#e There was also a hole in the root of the big tree.
#c 大樹的根部也有一個洞。
#e Then they both arrived at the root of the tree where there was a bee hive.
#c 然後他們來到了那棵有蜂窩的樹下面。
#e The dog barked furiously. He probably wanted to take the bee hive.
#c 這隻狗瘋狂地吠著，他可能是想要把蜂窩拿起來吧。
#e The boy knelt down and looked into the hole on the ground.
#c 這個男孩蹲下來往地洞裡看。
#e Looking into the hole, he was shocked, because a vole suddenly appeared from the hole.
#c 小男孩往洞裡看時嚇了一跳因為從洞裡突然出現了一隻田鼠。
#e Then the dog tried hard to shake the tree and make the bee hive fall. It seems that he wanted to eat it.
#c 然後狗用力地搖樹讓蜂窩掉下來。他可能是想吃那個蜂窩。
#n 此處slualu可能為口誤。說者應想說slugelu "搖晃"。
#e Because the dog shaked the tree, all the bees which were inside the hive came out.
#c 因為狗搖了那棵樹，所有原本在蜂窩裡面的蜜蜂都跑到外面了。
#e So, because the dog shaked the tree, the bee hive fell to the ground, and all the bees came out.
#c 所以因為狗去搖樹，蜂窩掉到了地上，導致所有蜜蜂都跑了出來。
#n maanu di 是說錯話時用來更正自己的用語，譯為"什麼啦?/不是啦!"
#e The vole from the hole was also shocked after seeing the bees that came out, because they sting people.
#c 連在地洞裡的老鼠看到蜜蜂出來也嚇了一跳，他們是會叮人的。
#e The boy also climbed up the tree with a hole on the root.
#c 這男孩也爬上這棵根部有大洞的樹。
#n 是爬到樹上看的
#e He climbed up the tree to see into the hole, wondering what's in there.
#c 他爬上樹去，看著那個洞穴，心想洞穴裡面到底是有什麼。
#e Probably the frog went hiding there, he thought.
#c 他猜想著青蛙可能躲到洞裡去了。
#e An owl suddenly came out from the hole.
#c 有一隻貓頭鷹突然從樹洞裡飛出來。
#n 此處qsaan應為口誤，應為saan。
#e The child went to see what's in the hole, and perhaps he was shocked by something, he fell from the tree.
#c 小男孩跑去看洞裡面有什麼。也許是因為被嚇到了，便從樹上跌下來。
#e Now we see that the dog kept running and running, because he was chased by the bees.
#c 我們接著看到，這隻狗因為被蜜蜂追所以一直跑一直跑。
#e All the bees that came out were stinging him. So the dog was running away.
#c 所有蜜蜂都出來要叮他，所以狗逃跑。
#e The boy fell on the ground.
#c 這個小男孩跌落在地上。
#e There was a big stone on the road.
#c 然後，路上有一個大石頭。
#n qhuni "樹" 應為口誤。
#e The owl was flying, probably looking for him (the boy), too.
#c 貓頭鷹飛了起來，可能也是要找他(小男孩)。
#e The owl came looking for the little boy. It was flying high above, but he (the boy) didn't know.
#c 貓頭鷹來找小男孩。他也在上面飛。但他(小男孩)並不知道。
#e The boy grabbed the branches and calls for the frog.
#c 小男孩抓著樹枝且在那呼喊青蛙。
#n 此處snduruk應為口誤，說者亦於下一IU更正為sndurak。
#e The dog was afraid because he was chased by the bees.
#c 狗因為被蜜蜂追而顯得害怕。
#e Being afraid, the dog hid himself behind the stone.
#c 那隻狗很害怕，便躲到了石頭後面去。
#e And the boy, he was standing on the stone, calling for the frog.
#c 而小男孩則站在石頭上呼喊青蛙。
#e The owl was looking at the boy, staying on the branches behind him.
#c 貓頭鷹從男孩後面的樹枝上看著他。
#e Then we see that the dog went to the back of the stone, which made a deer shocked.
#c 接著我們看到狗跑到石頭後面去，因而嚇到了一隻鹿。
#e It was a very big deer that was behind the stone.
#c 原來是那麼大的一隻鹿在石頭後面。
#n tdiyan 原指動物被打獵用的陷阱吊到，此處指男孩被鹿角勾起。
#n urung 可指各種動物的角。urung dapa "牛角"。rurung miric "羊角"。
#e The boy was suddenly hooked by the antler.
#c 小男孩突然就被鹿角勾到了。
#e The dog shocked the deer, so it stood up, and the boy was scared and hooked up by the antler of the deer.
#c 因為狗去嚇到了鹿，鹿就站了起來。小男孩因此被嚇到，而且還被鹿角給勾了起來。
#e So the deer kept the boy on his antler.
#c 於是鹿把小男孩放在鹿角上。
#e He seems to be yelling "Put me down! Help me!"
#c 小男孩好像就大喊著：「放我下來！來幫我啊！」
#n s- 推測為一將介係詞類轉換成主動詞類之詞綴。s-b-bobo tudu tmalang ka laqi "小朋友在田梗上跑著"。
#e His dog is also running behind them.
#c 小男孩的狗也在後面跑。
#n 此處mddayo應為口誤。下一IU說者更正為mdayo。
#e Since the boy was being carried away by the deer, the dog seemed to be trying to help the boy.
#c 因為眼看著男孩就要被鹿給帶走了，看起來這隻狗是想幫忙的樣子。
#e The deer was big, so the dog seemed to be afraid of it as well.
#c 這隻鹿很大，所以狗看起來也很害怕。
#e They arrived at a cliff.
#c 他們到達了一處懸崖。
#e And the dog also fell off the precipice.
#c 所以狗也掉落到懸崖邊。
#e The deer threw the boy off the cliff.
#c 這隻鹿把小男孩丟下懸崖。
#e So the dog and the boy fell into a cave together.
#c 狗和小男孩便一起掉進一個岩洞裡。
#e Inside the cave was water. It was a river, or what we call a lake.
#c 洞裡有水，就是河流啊，或是我們所謂的湖泊。
#e There is also a big piece of wood on the water.
#c 在崖邊的湖水上有一塊大木頭。
#e So their original purpose was to look for the frog that ran away.
#c 所以他們原本的目的就是想要來找跑掉的青蛙。
#e Here we see the dog (down here), and the deer was looking at it from the top.
#c 我們看這狗呢，鹿正從上面看著他。
#e The dog and the boy fell into the water of the lake.
#c 狗和小男孩掉進了湖水裡。
#e After the boy got up, he sat there and put his dog on his head, carrying it.
#c 小男孩站起來後，便坐著。並且把狗放到頭上背。
#e They went to look for it (the frog) again, on the other side of the stones, where there was grass everywhere. They searched for the frog.
#c 他們又繼續尋找(青蛙)。在石堆的另一邊，那兒到處都是草。他們繼續學找青蛙。
#n 此處kiyan應為kingan。
#e The dog swam across, and there the boy found a rotten wood as he arrived.
#c 狗游了過去，到達時小拿還在那兒發現了一塊腐木。
#e "Keep quiet!" he told his dog. "It (the frog) might be right in there!" he said.
#c 他對狗說：「不要講話！」「青蛙可能就在裡面！」他說。
#e So the dog climbed over this rotten wood, and so did the boy.
#c 所以狗爬上了這根腐木，而男孩也是。
#e They are in the lake water.
#c 他們在湖水裡。
#e Since where they were at was the lake water, the boy and his dog climbed up this rotten wood.
#c 因為他們是在湖水之中，小男孩和他的狗便爬上這塊腐木。
#e In the same way they both climbed up this rotten wood.
#c 一樣地小男孩和狗都爬上了這個腐木。
#e Then, they looked (into the wood). What were they looking at?
#c 然後呢，他們就(往木頭裡面)看。他們在看什麼呢？
#e It was two frogs–the mother frog and her child.
#c 是兩隻青蛙–青蛙媽媽和他的孩子。
#n wawa專指動物的小孩。但狗及豬的小孩另有詞彙。前者為uruk，後者為beru。
#e They were sitting together behind the rotten wood.
#c 他們一起坐在腐木的後面。
#e Then, they came here again to see, the dog and the boy sitting on the rotten wood.
#c 然後，他們又來繼續看著。狗和小男孩都坐在腐木上。
#e They were happy to see so many children frogs. They came to see the mother frog and the children frogs.
#c 他們看到這麼多小青蛙很高興。他們來看著青蛙媽媽和這些小青蛙們。
#e There were also children frogs behind the mother. They were bigger ones.
#c 青蛙媽媽的後面也有小青蛙。他們是比較大的小青蛙。
#e All these frogs seem to be newly born babies.
#c 這些小青蛙看起來都是剛出生的。
#n tniyo 應為 tnugiyo "全部"。
#n so hari 此處譯為 "好像"、"似乎"。
#e The mother frog was very happy looking at her children, and the boy was happy too.
#c 青蛙媽媽看著她的孩子感到非常快樂。小男孩也是。
#e The dog and the boy were happy and surprised to see all the frogs, so they laughed loudly.
#c 狗和小男孩看到那麼多隻青蛙又驚又喜，他們於是大聲地笑出來。
#e "Here, we have found the forg that had been lost!" That's probably what the boy said.
#c 「我們找到遺失的青蛙了！」小男孩應該是那麼說的。
#e The boy then grabbed one frog that looked like the one that was originally living in his house.
#c 小男孩於是抓了一隻像本來在家裡的那隻青蛙。
#n srapun應為sdrapun。
#e The dog was very happy.
#c 這隻狗非常快樂。
#e The boy grabbed one frog, and ran back to his house, to put it in the house.
#c 小男孩用手抓一隻青蛙，跑回家，又把它放在家裡。
#e The frog on the other side ... it's not known whether the mother frog was actually the father frog.
#c 在另一邊的青蛙，不知道這隻青蛙媽媽是不是其實是青蛙爸爸？
#e Seven kid frogs sit behind this parent frog.
#c 有七隻小青蛙坐在後面。
#e They watched the kid frog being taken away by the boy.
#c 青蛙們看著被小男孩帶走的那隻小青蛙。
#e The parent frog seems to find it pitiful, crying out "wa ..." "It (my child) has been taken away my a human" he said.
#c 青蛙爸/媽好像心疼，他說：「小青蛙被人帶走啦！」。
#e But they all looked really happy, and laughed.
#c 但他們看起來都很高興，也笑了。
#e They guessed that this person wouldn't kill people, so he would not kill frogs either.
#c 他們猜想這人不會殺人，所以也不會把青蛙弄死。
#e So the two (parent) frogs, along with the seven kid frogs, stood there and said "goodbye, then."
#c 那兩隻青蛙和七隻小青蛙便站在那兒，說：「再見了！」。
#e The father frog and mother frog felt happy.
#c 青蛙爸爸和青蛙媽媽感到很高興。
#e So the story would probably end here.
#c 這個故事應該就到這裡。
#e The father frog and mother frog were not worried.
#c 青蛙爸爸和青蛙媽媽也不會擔心。
#e They guessed that the boy was kind-hearted.
#c 他們猜想這小男孩心腸很好。
#e The dog was very happy. He laughed, with his mouth widely open.
#c 狗很高興，張著嘴大笑。
#e So the story about the frog, the boy, and the dog ends here.
#c 青蛙、男孩和狗的故事就到這裡。
#e My story ends here.
#c 我就講到這邊。
